caption: I love to call ahead for some curbside pick up, the pastries are my absolute fave that I've had!!

I love this place and I go there as often as I can. It's pretty much the only place I'll actually get lunch to eat in these days, some things are worth even braving a pandemic.  Best pies in the Springfield area, and a wonderful variety of other pastries, sandwiches, and other things. Seriously, how many places hand-make their own croissants?  Oh yeah, and they have CHOCOLATE FILLED croissants. If I can get one of those, it makes my day.  Their lunch menu has a steady assortment of delicious salads and sandwiches. Tried 'em all. Would order any of them again..  I'm eating a slice of a Smore's pie right now that is so delicious that it's probably illegal in ten states. Last summer my family wound up eating a lot of pie because I was dead-set on trying to emulate their pie crust....

Everything I’ve tried has been delicious, but their kouign amann (a pastry I’d never heard of before) is truly outstanding. Great service, very easy to do curbside pickup during the pandemic,  plenty of parking right outside their door. And a little park across the street if you want to picnic — in fact, the owner offered to bring out a table for me on a beautiful March morning. Can’t be beat!

I have stopped in to grab a coffee and pastry a few times at Granny’s in the past few years. Each time I have felt welcomed and I leave with a delicious treat. I also wanted to share a story. I ordered a pumpkin pie during the holiday season last year (side note: my mouth is watering thinking about that pie). I got a reminder call from Granny’s that morning for pick up and realized I wouldn’t be able to get there in time. My husband did not want to miss out on that pie. So he called back and explained our dilemma. Granny’s stayed 45 minutes after close to get us that pie! They said they’d wait an hour and if we couldn’t get there in time, they’d donate the pie to a shelter or someone who could enjoy it for the holidays. Truly amazing people. The pies are great, the people even better!
This place is amazing! Everything that we have tried there is delicious. We definitely recommend it.

Some of the best pastries western mass has to offer. Excellent selection, almost all of which I've had after being a regular since they opened. Every slice is pie is the best slice of pie I've ever eaten. French pastries to die for. The Kouign Amann is legitimately the best baked good I've ever eaten in my life. If you ever are near Springfield, this place is easy to get to off of 91 or 291, and 100% always worth it. Some top notch people own and runs this place too, get into it.

I am always thrilled with my Granny’s purchased.  I tend to go for the sweet stuff rather than meals.  I usually get a cookie and some sort of scone.  They’re always delicious.  Yesterday I tried the bread pudding.  It was totally AMAZING!!!  I wish I had bought 2 of them!!  Now that I think about it, I once tried the made from scratch (everything is) monkey bread, because my daughter wanted it.  That also blew me away.  Only the highest recommendation for Granny’s.  Don’t miss it!!
Awesome
Try the almond croissant - it’s incredible. Also the beignets. It’s a really nice space and the owners are very impressive bakers. Wish I were in Springfield more often.

Although I have not stopped in yet the photos look nice the coffee probably good but after looking closer at the photo of the FIRST TURN DANISH DOUGH  I recognize that type of dough it is simply pre ready not a scratch made companies like SYSCO sorry about the review like this
From the superb customer service to the incomparably delicious pastries, my visit to Granny's could not have been more enjoyable! I would highly recommend the beignets.

Hi Todd!!!  The coffee is 11/10, the CROISSANTS are 11/10 and the service is 11/10. Absolutely wonderful place to be, I'm going back the second Amy drives me there. I wish I could have croissants from Granny's every day. Also, I am buying a t-shirt.  MUST VISIT SPOT IF YOU ARE IN SPRINGFIELD!!!
Everything is excellent and the people are great

I discovered this place only a few months ago and it was one of the best parts of 2020! The owners are very friendly and the food is fantastic. Definitely try the grit cups for breakfast and one of their signature sandwiches for lunch! Pour-over coffee is also really great quality and always made perfectly. I am excited to try all the menu items moving forward. Plenty of on street parking.
Fantastic business. The owner waited half hour after closing hours for me to pick up the pie my wife had ordered. Beyond the service, the pie itself was phenomenal. Looking forward to going back
Incredible pastries.
Nice, friendly and the baked goods are  so delicious. The beignets are to die for.
The beignets are to die for! That said, everything I've tried here has been wonderful. And the owner is lovely.
Incredible food, incredible owners, and incredible staff. The pies are amazing
The beignets were the best thing I’ve ever eaten🤤 all of the pastries i’ve tried have been delicious too

Literally everything on the menu is incredible! I had a sweet potato pie milkshake today and it was life changing, definitely a must have! But my all time favorite treat there is the bread pudding, it just taste like love!

Incredible pastries!! I ordered a cheese danish, bear claw, chocolate croissants, and kouign-amann. They were so soft, flakey, buttery, sweet and creamy. Don’t miss their beignets on Friday. They also serve locally roasted coffee from Monsoon Roasters; a delightful touch and incredible pairing with these fine pastries. Highly recommend!!!

Flaky, delicious pastry. Exceptional croissants, macaroons to die for, fluffy beignets, amazing pies ...   I could on and on. Love their values and community spirit especially during these difficult times.

Went in for lunch and had a very good experience.  Food was very good and service was fast, there is plenty of on street parking.  The location is fairly small with limited dine in seating, but it is worth the visit.  The prices on their sandwiches are very reasonable, and the food is very fresh.
The beignets are so GOOD!!! I also had the pulled pork biscuit sandwich and it was fresh and delicious. I highly recommend this place 🤩
Delicious fried chicken sandwich on a biscuit .... Oh Lawdy !
Great space. Friendly proprietors.  And WONDERFUL pastries and sandwiches. Very creative and fresh. Highly recommend

Comfort far beyond the food. Won't stop RAVING about this places for weeks to come!!! Can personally recommend the Oh Lawdy but would say with certainty that anything you order will blow your socks off!
Fresh pastry. Nice spot to grab a quick lunch and a coffee.

Diligently baked french pastries and cooked southern sandwiches... do I need to say more? OK fine... my kids love the beignets and enjoy the down home friendly feel and I love being the hero of my office parties for bringing delicious pastries.
World class baked goods tucked into a charming side street shop. Great atmosphere. Good coffee.
World class bakery in downtown. Warm, inviting space and delicious coffee, pastries, pies, and lunch options! Locally owned. Big community table.
it's all delicious !
Nice place with great food! 100% Recommend!
Warm hospitality. Great croissants, quiches and slices of pie today. More next time. Sit, eat, chat. Exciting new place! Go, Springfield!
The best muffins I have ever had! Not dry at all and moist with plenty of chips Reasonable prices too
Such a great spot. Very cozy atmosphere and the baked goods are delicious!!
Pies, pastries, and great lunch sandwiches!

Granny's Baking Table is such a great spot. It is warm, welcoming, and cozy. And, those pastries...the almond croissant was amazing and then I couldn't resist the beignets. They were hot and soft and gooey with melted confectioners sugar on top. So delicious. Please check this spot out.

Granny's has the best frosnapper (Danish pastry) on this side of the Atlantic. The croissants are buttery and flakey and the beignets are better than in New Orleans. These are the best pastries I've ever eaten, and everything is made with love and care!
